{"batchcomplete": "", "query": {"pages": {"8425661": {"pageid": 8425661, "ns": 0, "title": "Mamma Mia! (film)", "contentmodel": "wikitext", "pagelanguage": "en", "pagelanguagehtmlcode": "en", "pagelanguagedir": "ltr", "touched": "2026-02-19T02:23:21Z", "lastrevid": 1339131051, "length": 51105, "fullurl": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mamma_Mia!_(film)", "editurl": "https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Mamma_Mia!_(film)&action=edit", "canonicalurl": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mamma_Mia!_(film)", "pageprops": {"defaultsort": "Mamma Mia! (Film)", "displaytitle": "<i>Mamma Mia!</i> (film)", "page_image": "Mamma_Mia_(2008)_US_poster.jpg", "wikibase-shortdesc": "2008 film by Phyllida Lloyd", "wikibase_item": "Q188850"}, "description": "2008 film by Phyllida Lloyd", "descriptionsource": "local", "extract": "Mamma Mia! (promoted as Mamma Mia! The Movie) is a 2008 jukebox musical romantic comedy film directed by Phyllida Lloyd and written by Catherine Johnson, based on her book from the 1999 musical of the same name. The film features an ensemble cast, including Meryl Streep, Pierce Brosnan, Colin Firth, Stellan Skarsgård, Julie Walters, Dominic Cooper, Amanda Seyfried, and Christine Baranski. The film follows a young bride-to-be named Sophie who invites three men to her upcoming wedding, with the possibility that any of them could be her real father.\nPrincipal photography primarily took place on the island of Skopelos, Greece, from August to September 2007, with ABBA members Benny Andersson and Björn Ulvaeus composing the film's score. Mamma Mia! premiered at the Leicester Square in London on June 30, 2008, before being released in the United Kingdom on July 10, and in the United States on July 18, by Universal Pictures. It received mixed reviews from critics and was a box-office success, grossing $610 million worldwide on a $52 million budget, becoming the fifth highest-grossing film of 2008. A sequel, titled Mamma Mia! Here We Go Again, was released on July 20, 2018, with much of the cast returning.", "categories": [{"ns": 14, "title": "Category:2000s buddy comedy films"}, {"ns": 14, "title": "Category:2000s female buddy films"}, {"ns": 14, "title": "Category:2000s musical comedy films"}, {"ns": 14, "title": "Category:2000s romantic musical films"}, {"ns": 14, "title": "Category:2008 American films"}, {"ns": 14, "title": "Category:2008 British films"}, {"ns": 14, "title": "Category:2008 English-language films"}, {"ns": 14, "title": "Category:2008 German films"}, {"ns": 14, "title": "Category:2008 directorial debut films"}, {"ns": 14, "title": "Category:2008 films"}, {"ns": 14, "title": "Category:2008 musical films"}, {"ns": 14, "title": "Category:2008 romantic comedy films"}, {"ns": 14, "title": "Category:ABBA"}, {"ns": 14, "title": "Category:All Wikipedia articles written in American English"}, {"ns": 14, "title": "Category:All articles with unsourced statements"}, {"ns": 14, "title": "Category:American buddy comedy films"}, {"ns": 14, "title": "Category:American female buddy films"}, {"ns": 14, "title": "Category:American musical comedy films"}, {"ns": 14, "title": "Category:American romantic comedy films"}, {"ns": 14, "title": "Category:American romantic musical films"}, {"ns": 14, "title": "Category:Articles with short description"}, {"ns": 14, "title": "Category:Articles with unsourced statements from January 2017"}, {"ns": 14, "title": "Category:British buddy comedy films"}, {"ns": 14, "title": "Category:British female buddy films"}, {"ns": 14, "title": "Category:British musical comedy films"}, {"ns": 14, "title": "Category:British romantic comedy films"}, {"ns": 14, "title": "Category:British romantic musical films"}, {"ns": 14, "title": "Category:CS1 errors: generic title"}, {"ns": 14, "title": "Category:English-language German films"}, {"ns": 14, "title": "Category:English-language buddy comedy films"}, {"ns": 14, "title": "Category:English-language musical comedy films"}, {"ns": 14, "title": "Category:English-l